# Moodify Health (monorepo) conventions

- Repo apps:
  - `health-back/`: Express + Prisma (PostgreSQL), TypeScript source in `src/**/*.ts`
  - `health-front/`: Next.js App Router, Tailwind v4, PWA via `next-pwa` (webpack mode)
- Prefer **TypeScript** everywhere. Don’t add compiled outputs (`dist/`, `.next/`) to git.
- Keep API changes consistent across:
  - backend route + middleware
  - frontend proxy route (if needed)
  - frontend pages/components consuming it
- Auth model:
  - backend issues JWT
  - frontend stores JWT in **httpOnly cookie** and attaches `Authorization: Bearer <token>` when calling backend server-side.
- RBAC model:
  - UI should hide/disable admin/super-admin entry points if user lacks access
  - server layouts/pages must still enforce access (redirect/403) even if UI hides links

